<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,151,824]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,584,608]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for Francisco Romero (Maracay, 
<collectingCountry box="[990,1107,583,607]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
) who collected the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,583,607]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen and whose collection supplied important information on the distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[1151,1278,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1151,1278,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Philaethria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,270,655,679]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,151,824]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,506,691,716]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[519,639,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romeroi">
<emphasis box="[519,639,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. romeroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from Rancho Grande in the state of Aragua in N. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,266,727,751]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
at 
<quantity box="[301,385,727,751]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
above sea level in montane forest habitats. It is probable that 
<taxonomicName box="[1083,1198,729,752]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romeroi">
<emphasis box="[1083,1198,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. romeroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may occur along the Cordillera de La Costa. 
<taxonomicName box="[419,533,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romeroi">
<emphasis box="[419,533,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. romeroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flies sympatrically with 
<emphasis box="[813,908,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. o s t a r a</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[966,1054,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. n e il di</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,151,824]" box="[197,696,799,824]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,577,799,824]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hostplant and immature stages.</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
